    "title": "GAA Unveils 30-Year Plan to Transform Maurice Bishop International Airport",
    "dek": "Maurice Bishop International Airport (MBIA), Grenada’s primary gateway to the world, is in the midst of a significant transformation as part of an ambitious …",
    "section": "news",
    "publishedAt": "2025-02-14",
    "draft": false,
    "content": "Maurice Bishop International Airport (MBIA), Grenada’s primary gateway to the world, is in the midst of a significant transformation as part of an ambitious 30-year master plan. This comprehensive redevelopment, led by the Grenada Airport Authority (GAA) under the guidance of its Chief Executive Officer (CEO), Edgar Stephen, aims to revolutionise the airport’s infrastructure, operations, and services to support Grenada’s long-term economic growth, tourism, and trade. The plan is set to make MBIA one of the most advanced and efficient airports in the Caribbean region.",
